00:22:20.249 --> 00:22:21.600
about the question.

00:22:21.600 --> 00:22:24.820
My favorite examples of feelings of knowing
is when a word is on the tip of your tongue.

00:22:24.820 --> 00:22:30.229
On the one hand, so annoying, drives me crazy
every single time, you know, you're walking

00:22:30.229 --> 00:22:34.799
down the street, you see someone, you know
you know their name but you just can't quite

00:22:34.799 --> 00:22:36.460
place it.

00:22:36.460 --> 00:22:41.639
So frustrating, but it's also kind of profound
because how do you know you know their name

00:22:41.639 --> 00:22:43.289
if you don't actually know it?

00:22:43.289 --> 00:22:45.769
[Laughter]
&gt;&gt;Jonah Lehrer: Why are you so convinced that

00:22:45.769 --> 00:22:49.460
memories in one of these overstuffed filing
cabinets if you can't find the file?

00:22:49.460 --> 00:22:51.879
Well, that's a feeling of knowing.

00:22:51.879 --> 00:22:56.979
It's a hunch reminding you that if you just
keep on searching for that name, in 5 minutes

00:22:56.979 --> 00:23:00.679
or 10 minutes, you will find it, you will
locate the file.

00:23:00.679 --> 00:23:05.299
That feeling of knowing will become real will
become actual knowledge.

00:23:05.299 --> 00:23:09.470
Now, when it becomes to creative problem solving,
