00:23:09.470 --> 00:23:14.639
essential guide because study after study
has found that when it comes to problems that

00:23:14.639 --> 00:23:18.940
don't require moments of insight, that people
can actually diagnose, about 85 percent of

00:23:18.940 --> 00:23:23.039
the time, whether or not they can solve a
problem within a given time frame.

00:23:23.039 --> 00:23:27.299
So I can show you analytical creative problem
and say, "Can you solve this in an hour?

00:23:27.299 --> 00:23:28.470
Can you solve this in a day?

00:23:28.470 --> 00:23:30.350
Can you solve this in a week?"

00:23:30.350 --> 00:23:34.859
With 85 percent accuracy, and upwards of 85
percent accuracy in many domains, people can

00:23:34.859 --> 00:23:37.710
say, "Yep, I can do that, no problem."

00:23:37.710 --> 00:23:39.559
Or, "No, I can't."

00:23:39.559 --> 00:23:42.919
Now what makes these feelings of knowing even
